# ClipRelay

ClipRelay is a desktop application for recording audio, transcribing speech to text (using OpenAI Whisper models), and quickly sending or copying the results for use in chat or code editors like VS Code.

## Features

- Record audio and transcribe it to text using different Whisper models (Tiny, Base, Small, Medium, Large).
- Copy the transcribed text with a custom prefix for chat relay.
- Send the transcription directly to ChatGPT.
- Focus and paste the transcription into VS Code automatically.
- Choose and remember your preferred Whisper model and window position.
- Simple, user-friendly interface with icons for each action.

## Requirements

- Python 3.8+
- Tkinter (usually included with Python)
- [OpenAI Whisper](https://github.com/openai/whisper) and its dependencies
- Other dependencies: see `requirements.txt`

## Installation

1. Clone this repository:
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/clipRelay.git cd clipRelay
   
2. Install dependencies:
   pip install -r requirements.txt

## Usage

1. Run the application:
   python main.py
2. Use the interface to record, transcribe, copy, send, or paste your text.

## Configuration & Settings

- User settings (window size, position, last used model, etc.) are saved automatically in a JSON file.
- You can add or remove unwanted phrases from the transcription filter in `audioService.py` (see `PHRASES_A_SUPPRIMER`).

## Customization

- To change icons, replace the PNG files in the `img/` folder.
- To add more unwanted phrases for filtering, edit the list in `audioService.py`.

